# Design System Guidelines

## Color System
- **Primary**: Use `bg-primary` and `text-primary` for main actions and key elements
- **Surface levels**: Use `bg-surface-0` through `bg-surface-24` for layered components
- **Text colors**: Always use semantic colors like `text-on-surface`, `text-on-primary`, etc.
- **Borders**: Use `border-outline` or `border-outline-variant` for consistent borders

## Typography
- **Headlines**: Use `text-headline-large/medium/small` for section headers
- **Titles**: Use `text-title-large/medium/small` for component titles
- **Body**: Use `text-body-large/medium/small` for content text
- **Labels**: Use `text-label-large/medium/small` for form labels and captions

## Elevation & Shadows
- **Shadows**: Use `shadow-elevation-1` through `shadow-elevation-24` 
- **Surface elevation**: Combine surface colors with elevation shadows
- **Interactive states**: Increase elevation on hover/focus

## Spacing & Layout
- **Consistent gaps**: Use standard spacing scale (4, 6, 8, 12, 16, 24)
- **Component padding**: Use `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8` for component containers
- **Section spacing**: Use `py-24` for major sections, `py-12` for subsections

## Component Structure
- **Container pattern**: Outer container with padding, inner content with gaps
- **State management**: Handle loading, error, disabled states consistently
- **Accessibility**: Include proper ARIA labels and keyboard navigation

## Interactive Elements
- **Buttons**: Use defined button variants (primary, ghost, glow)
- **Focus states**: Always include visible focus indicators
- **Hover effects**: Subtle elevation or color changes
- **Transitions**: Use `transition-all duration-200` for smooth animations

## Form Components
- **Input styling**: Use consistent border radius and padding
- **Error states**: Show error with `text-error` and `border-error`
- **Labels**: Always pair inputs with descriptive labels
- **Helper text**: Provide guidance with `text-body-small text-on-surface-variant`

## Cards & Containers
- **Background**: Use `bg-surface` or elevation surfaces
- **Borders**: Use `border-outline-variant` for subtle definition
- **Radius**: Use `rounded-lg` (12px) for most components
- **Shadows**: Apply appropriate elevation shadows